<section xml:id="cba-project-bank">
  <title>Project Ideas for Mathematical Investigations</title>

  <p>
    The following project ideas are examples of investigations that students may choose
    from when completing a Classroom-Based Assessment (CBA). Each project allows students
    to demonstrate problem-solving, modelling, reasoning, and communication skills.
  </p>

  <p>
    Students are encouraged to adapt these ideas, collect their own data, and develop
    their own approaches. The quality of the investigation will be judged against the
    learning outcomes and expectations for students.
  </p>

  <ol>
    <li><p>How can I determine the volume of my home hot-water tank without opening it?</p></li>
    <li><p>Is the diameter of a circular object better found by measuring circumference or width?</p></li>
    <li><p>How accurate is my estimate of the height of a room using shadows?</p></li>
    <li><p>What is the relationship between the floor area and perimeter of a rectangular room?</p></li>
    <li><p>Can I calculate the volume of a cupboard or press using indirect measurements?</p></li>
    <li><p>How consistent are measurements taken by different students using the same method?</p></li>
    <li><p>How much water is used in a standard shower, and how can it be estimated?</p></li>
    <li><p>Can I estimate the height of my house using similar triangles?</p></li>
    <li><p>How accurate is a measuring tape compared to a ruler for long distances?</p></li>
    <li><p>How does the surface area of a box change when its dimensions are doubled?</p></li>

    <li><p>Is phone battery percentage proportional to charging time?</p></li>
    <li><p>Does mobile data usage increase linearly with screen time?</p></li>
    <li><p>How does the cost of electricity scale with usage in my home?</p></li>
    <li><p>Are supermarket discounts always what they claim to be?</p></li>
    <li><p>How does scaling a recipe affect ingredient quantities?</p></li>
    <li><p>Is pocket money spending consistent from week to week?</p></li>
    <li><p>How accurate are fuel efficiency claims for cars?</p></li>
    <li><p>How does screen brightness affect phone battery drain?</p></li>
    <li><p>Is step count proportional to distance walked?</p></li>
    <li><p>How does household water usage change with family size?</p></li>

    <li><p>Can phone battery charging be modelled using a linear equation?</p></li>
    <li><p>Is the cooling of a hot drink linear over time?</p></li>
    <li><p>How does savings grow with regular weekly deposits?</p></li>
    <li><p>Can I model the cost of school lunches over a month?</p></li>
    <li><p>Does internet speed vary predictably during the day?</p></li>
    <li><p>Can exam revision time be predicted from study habits?</p></li>
    <li><p>How does queue length affect waiting time?</p></li>
    <li><p>Is there a pattern in bus arrival times?</p></li>
    <li><p>Can algebra be used to model score progression in a game?</p></li>
    <li><p>How does temperature change during a typical school day?</p></li>

    <li><p>How consistent are daily step counts over a week?</p></li>
    <li><p>What is the most common daily screen time among students in my class?</p></li>
    <li><p>How reliable is sleep tracking data?</p></li>
    <li><p>Do students estimate lengths accurately?</p></li>
    <li><p>How does reaction time vary between students?</p></li>
    <li><p>Is there a relationship between homework time and test results?</p></li>
    <li><p>How accurate are short-term weather forecasts?</p></li>
    <li><p>What is the distribution of shoe sizes in my class?</p></li>
    <li><p>How much variation is there in daily phone usage?</p></li>
    <li><p>Are studentsâ€™ travel times to school similar or very different?</p></li>
  </ol>
